Small Artificial Data set

Source: R/dataSets.R

Small Toy Example Data set which was used by Sanz-Mateo et.al.

Format

The format is: int [1:13, 1:7] 10 12 17 21 9 12 12 14 13 15 ... - attr(*, "dimnames")=List of 2 ..$ : chr [1:13] "1" "2" "3" "4" ... ..$ : chr [1:7] "1" "2" "3" "4" ...

Examples


data(casc1)
casc1
#>     1 2 3 4 5 6  7
#> 1  10 4 6 2 1 0  4
#> 2  12 3 7 1 2 1 -1
#> 3  17 2 5 1 3 1 -2
#> 4  21 2 8 2 4 1 -1
#> 5   9 3 3 3 5 1 -4
#> 6  12 4 7 3 6 0 -3
#> 7  12 4 6 3 7 0  4
#> 8  14 3 7 3 6 0 -5
#> 9  13 3 6 3 5 4 -1
#> 10 15 3 7 5 4 3  3
#> 11 17 2 6 7 3 2 -2
#> 12 17 3 8 7 2 1 -2
#> 13 18 4 6 7 1 1 -1
